body:
although this is convenient, it does use up a valuable argument slot. we could achieve the same thing with a uprobe:

```bpftrace
uprobe:bitcoind:"CChainState::ConnectBlock(CBlock const&, BlockValidationState&, CBlockIndex*, CCoinsViewCache&, CChainParams const&, bool)" 
{ 
    @connect_start = nsecs;
}

usdt:bitcoind:validation:block_connected
{
    @t = nsecs - @connect_start;
}
```

(untested)

alternatively if we want a more stable interface we could just stick a usdt at the start as well.

